<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
</IN>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian steel ingot production totaled 288,032
metric tons in the week ended April 28, up 0.5% from 286,668
tons in the preceding week but down 12% from 328,754 tons a
year earlier, Statistics Canada, a federal agency, said.
   The cumulative total in 1990 was 4.6 million tons, down
13% from 5.3 million tons a year earlier. A metric ton is
equal to about 2,204.6 pounds.
</LP>
