<HL>
   Business Brief -- Interco Inc.:
   Furniture Maker Says Banks
   To Extend Loan Payments
</HL>
<DATE>
05/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B8
</SO>
<CO>
   ISS
</CO>
<LP>
   Interco Inc. said its banks agreed to extend to Oct. 1
certain loan payments that were due today, including a $225.9
million payment on its bridge loan.
   Interco, which is suffering from a heavy debt and interest
burden, said the loan waiver extension will allow time to
complete an amendment to its existing bank credit agreement.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The maker of furniture and shoes also said its board will
consider "additional restructuring proposals" at a meeting
Wednesday. It didn't elaborate.
   Interco borrowed heavily in late 1988 to pay special
dividends to shareholders and fend off a takeover threat.
Asset sales have been less successful than expected.
</TEXT>
