<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Warren E. Buffett, chairman of Berkshire Hathaway Inc.,
said he controls an 11.04% stake in PS Group Inc.'s common
stock for investment purposes.
   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,
Mr. Buffett said that three companies he controls, National
Indemnity Co., National Liability &amp; Fire Insurance Co. and
Columbia Insurance Co., together hold 603,275 PS Group common
shares, including 373,575 shares bought March 16 to April 25
for $32.125 to $32.50 each.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Buffett said the PS Group shares were bought for
"investment purposes only."
   George Shortley, PS Group's president and chief executive,
said the San Diego, Calif., aircraft leasing and energy
company was pleased by Mr. Buffett's investment.
