    UTILITIES
                                                                                                       

    1ST QTR. 1990           1ST QTR. 1989        % CHG.
                                                                                                       

      6,974,929               6,917,457           +  1
                                                                                                       

   Several phone companies reported hefty earnings gains, but
a few had declines, primarily because of higher expenses.
   United Telecommunications showed strong improvement in its
long-distance business. So did MCI Communications, despite
heavy capital investment and a steeper effective tax rate. U
S West, Bell Atlantic and Nynex reported solid gains, aided
by non-telephone operations such as cellular service. Nynex
results would have been even higher except for a $39 million
pretax charge for an early-retirement program.
                                                                                                       

