    1ST QTR. 1990           1ST QTR. 1989        % CHG.
                                                                                                       

      1,344,390               1,197,636           + 12
                                                                                                       

   ITT called its results "better than expected"; profit
before tax and interest on all businesses except electronic
parts equaled or exceeded year-ago levels. The latest quarter
reflected a $47 million gain on the sale of its investment in
Compagnie Generale d'Electricite. Without the gain, net grew
3%. At Textron, "balanced diversity" gave it "a good start on
the year, despite softness in several of our markets," the
company said. Continued strength in finance and insurance
more than offset the current slowdown in its automotive
divisions. Per-share net was flat as shares outstanding rose
4%. GE continued double-digit earnings growth into a fourth
consecutive year, though NBC broadcasting reported "somewhat"
lower revenue and profit and the materials unit was weak.
   Candice Eggerss of Morgan Stanley is estimating $4.90 a
share for GE in 1990, up 12% from $4.36 in 1989. With the com
pany's stock buy-back program and productivity improvements,
"I'm confident of double-digit {earnings} improvement this
year," she says.
                                                                                                       

