<IN>
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
SECURITIES INDUSTRY (SCR)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- The New York Stock Exchange announced three
new stock listings, the American Stock Exchange two and the
National Market System of the over-the counter market four.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   On the Big Board, Hartford Steam Boiler Inspection &amp;
Insurance Co., a Hartford, Conn., engineering service and
insurance firm, will begin trading Wednesday under HSB.
                                                                                                       

   Northwestern Public Service Co., a Huron, S.D.,
electricity and natural gas utility, joins the New York
exchange tomorrow under NPS.
                                                                                                       

   Union Dominion Realty Trust Inc., a Richmond, Va., real
estate investment trust, begins trading today under the
symbol UDR. Joining the Amex is Interchange Financial
Services Corp., a Saddle Brook, N.J., bank holding company,
under ISB.
                                                                                                       

   United-Guardian Inc., a Hauppauge, N.Y., pharmaceuticals
company, began trading under UG. The five new Big Board and
Amex companies previously traded over the counter. On the OTC
market, Aspect Telecommunications Corp., a San Jose, Calif.,
telephone transaction-systems maker, began trading under
ASPT.
                                                                                                       

   Dynasty Classics Corp., a Carson, Calif., home decorating
products firm, started trading under DNST.
                                                                                                       

   IG Laboratories Inc., a Framingham, Mass., genetic testing
services firm, was listed under IGLI.
                                                                                                       

   Immune Response Corp., a San Diego biopharmaceutical
company, began trading under the symbol IMNR. The Amex also
opened trading on a second offering of put warrants by
Salomon Inc., based on the Financial Times Stock Exchange
100-share index, under the symbol FTP.WS. And the American
exchange began trading put and call options on the shares of
Tonka Corp. Options give the holder the right but not the
obligation to buy or sell shares of a company at a set price
within a certain period.
</TEXT>
